Source code lines should not exceed 80 characters

Use 4 (four) spaces for indentation (No tabs)

Files should end with an empty newline

Use UNIX style line endings (a single LF)

Ensure that your code adheres to the existing style in the project sources.
Refer to the GNU Coding Standards (https://www.gnu.org/prep/standards) for the
recommended coding standards for this project.

Commit messages should have a single-line synopsis followed by a verbose
description after an empty line. It is desirable that the first line is no
longer than 67 symbols.
